              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 457,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Humanoid creatures reason and act much like humans. They typically stand upright and have two arms and two legs.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "40b5d9c5e49dbe2aea5d7ecf38d950f3",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Mythic",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                "aonid": 232,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "War of Immortals",
              "page": 69,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Options with this trait grant or utilize mythic power. Feats with the mythic trait can only be taken by mythic characters, who are typically characters with a mythic Calling.  \n  \n Monsters with the mythic trait have access to a pool of Mythic Points and are particularly strong for creatures of their level. Many mythic monsters are either resistant or entirely immune to attacks from non-mythic creatures and weapons.  \n  \n Spells with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to be cast, and items with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to use their activated abilities.  \n  \n Weapons with the mythic trait overcome the resistances and immunities of mythic monsters.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 240,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "2f06cdb28a00932f4831579d535d58c6",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "tengu",
              "aonid": 83,
              "game-obj": "Ancestries",
              "name": "tengu",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Tengu",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "1.1",
                "aonid": 227,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "1.1",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 318",
                "aonid": 227,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 318",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core 2",
              "page": 318,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "A creature with this trait is a member of the tengu ancestry. Tengu are humanoids who resemble crows. An ability with this trait can be used or selected only by tengu. An item with this trait is created and used by tengu.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
